title: Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators
text: > Sports Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators The manes of a horse are tied in knots prior to a veterinary checkup at the Military Boekelo, eastern Netherlands, Wednesday, Oct. 7, 2015. More than 60,000 spectators enjoyed a day of Olympic-standard equestrian competition when they attended the Military Boekelo, one of the biggest sporting events held in the Netherlands. Eventing competition consists of dressage, cross-country and show jumping and competitors were seeking a spot at the Rio Olympics at the picturesque competition held near the city of Enschede. (AP Photo/Peter Dejong)
